s]] is appointed Director of the [[National Library of the Argentine Republic]].\n*[[July 14]] \u2013 Director [[Stephen Joseph]] sets up Britain's first [[theatre in the round]] at [[Scarborough, North Yorkshire]], predecessor of the [[Stephen Joseph Theatre]].<ref>{{Cite web |first=Simon |last=Murgatroyd |title=Scarborough In The Round |url=http://www.theatre-in-the-round.co.uk/index.html |accessdate=2015-11-23}}</ref>\n*[[July 30]] \u2013 The English poet [[Philip Larkin]], having become University Librarian at the [[University of Hull]] on March 21, takes a train from [[Kingston upon Hull|Hull]] to [[Grantham]], which inspires his poem \"[[The Whitsun Weddings (poem)|The Whitsun Weddings]]\".<ref>Contrary to his later recollection of the event. {{Cite book |editor=Burnett, Archie |title=The Complete Poems of Philip Larkin |location=London |publisher=Faber |year=2012 |isbn=978-0-571-24006-7 |page=411}}</ref> His collection ''[[The Less Deceived]]'' is published in November (dated October).\n*August \u2013 American [[speculative fiction]] author [[Charles Beaumont]]'s short story \"The Crooked Man\", depicting a homosexual society where heterosexuality is persecuted, is published in ''[[Playboy]]'' magazine after being rejected by ''[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]]''.\n*[[August 3]] \u2013 The English-language premi\u00e8re of [[Samuel Beckett]]'s play ''[[Waiting for Godot]]'', directed by [[Peter Hall (director)|Peter Hall]], opens at the [[Arts Theatre]], London.\n*[[August 27]] \u2013 The first hardback edition of ''[[Guinness World Records|The Guinness Book of Records]]'' appears in London.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Guinness Book History 1950 \u2013 Present |url=http://spyhunter007.com/spy_guinness_book_history.htm |accessdate=2012-02-10}}</ref>\n*September \u2013 ''[[Lolita]]'' by [[Vladimir Nabokov]] is published in Paris, three years before its US publication.<ref>{{Cite book |first=Brian |last=Boyd |title=Vladimir Nabokov: The American Years |publisher=Princeton University Press |year=1991 |isbn=0-691-06797-X |page=[https://archive.org/details/vladimirnabokova00boyd/page/226 226] |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/vladimirnabokova00boyd }}</ref>\n*November \u2013 [[Frank Herbert]]'s first novel ''[[The Dragon in the Sea]]'' begins a three-part serialization as ''Under Pressure'' in the monthly ''[[Analog Science Fiction and Fact|Astounding Science-Fiction]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.kirjasto.sci.fi/fherbert.htm |title=Frank (Patrick) Herbert |website=Books and Writers |first=Petri |last=Liukkonen |publisher=[[Kuusankoski]] Public Library |location=Finland |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427010107/http://www.kirjasto.sci.fi/fherbert.htm|archivedate=2014-04-27 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n*[[November 28]] \u2013 [[Ray Lawler]]'s ''[[Summer of the Seventeenth Doll]]'' receives its stage premi\u00e8re by the [[Melbourne Theatre Company|Union Theatre Repertory Company]] in [[Melbourne]] with the playwright in a lead. It is the first authentically naturalistic modern drama in the [[theatre of Australia]].<ref>{{Cite book |first=Peter |last=Fitzpatrick |title=After The Doll: Australian Drama Since 1955 |publisher=Edward Arnold Australia |location=Melbourne |year=1979 |series=Studies in Australian culture |isbn=0726720402 |page=[https://archive.org/details/afterthedollaust0000fitz/page/ vii] |url=https://archive.org/details/afterthedollaust0000fitz/page/ }}</ref>\n\n''Uncertain dates''\n*[[Jean Cocteau]] is elected to the ''[[Acad\u00e9mie fran\u00e7aise]]'' (March 3; inducted October 20) and to the ''[[The Royal Academies for Science and the Arts of Belgium|Acad\u00e9mie royale des Sciences, des Lettres et des Beaux-Arts de Belgique]]'' (January 8/October 1).\n*An article in the ''[[British Journal of Education]]'' criticises [[Enid Blyton]]'s novels as [[formula fiction|formulaic]].<ref>{{Cite book |first=Robert |last=Druce |title=This Day Our Daily Fictions: an enquiry into the multi-million bestseller status of Enid Blyton and Ian Fleming |location=Amsterdam |publisher=Rodopi |year=1992 |chapter=Chapter 4 |isbn=90-5183-401-2 |series=Costerus, n. s. vol. 84.}}</ref>\n*The Indian guru [[Mani Madhava Chakyar]] performs [[Koodiyattam]] outside a temple for the first time.<ref>{{Cite book |last=Bhargavinilayam |first=Das |title=Mani Madhaveeyam |publisher=Department of Cultural Affairs, [[Government of Kerala]] |year=1999 |isbn=81-86365-78-8}}</ref>\n\n==New books==\n===Fiction===\n[[File:Lolita 1955.JPG|thumb|1st ed.]]\n*[[Kingsley Amis]] \u2013 ''[[That Uncertain Feeling (novel)|That Uncertain Feeling]]''\n*[[Isaac Asimov]]\n**''[[The End of Eternity]]''\n**''[[The Martian Way and Other Stories]]''\n*[[Elisabeth Augustin]] \u2013 ''Labyrinth (Auswege)''\n*[[Nigel Balchin]] \u2013 ''[[The Fall of the Sparrow]]''\n*[[Antoine Blondin]] \u2013 ''[[L'Humeur vagabonde]]''\n*[[Leigh Brackett]] \u2013 ''[[The Long Tomorrow (novel)|The Long Tomorrow]]''\n*[[Ray Bradbury]] \u2013 ''[[The October Country]]''\n*[[Henry Cecil Leon|Henry Cecil]] \u2013 ''[[Brothers in Law (novel)|Brothers in Law]]''\n*[[Louis-Ferdinand C\u00e9line]] \u2013 ''[[Conversations with Professor Y]] (Entretiens avec le professeur Y)''\n*[[Agatha Christie]] \u2013 ''[[Hickory Dickory Dock (novel)|Hickory Dickory Dock]]''\n*[[Arthur C. Clarke]] \u2013 ''[[Earthlight]]''\n*[[Ivy Compton-Burnett]] \u2013 ''Mother and Son''\n*[[Thomas B. Costain]] \u2013 ''The Tontine''\n*[[Marco Denevi]] \u2013 ''Rosaura a las 10'' (Rosaura at 10 O'Clock)\n*[[Patrick Dennis]] \u2013 ''[[Auntie Mame]]''\n*[[John Dickson Carr]] \u2013 ''Captain Cut-Throat''\n*[[J. P. Donleavy]] \u2013 ''[[The Ginger Man]]''\n*[[Friedrich D\u00fcrrenmatt]] \u2013 ''[[Once a Greek]] (Grieche sucht Griechin)''\n*[[Mircea Eliade]] \u2013 ''[[The Forbidden Forest]] (Noaptea de S\u00e2nziene)''\n*[[Ian Fleming]] \u2013 ''[[Moonraker (novel)|Moonraker]]''\n*[[Andr\u00e9 Franquin]] \u2013 ''La Corne de rhinoc\u00e9ros''\n*[[Gillian Freeman]] \u2013 ''The Liberty Man''\n*[[William Gaddis]] \u2013 ''[[The Recognitions]]''\n*[[Gao Yubao]] (with Guo Yongjiang) \u2013 ''Gao Yubao''\n*[[David Garnett]] \u2013 ''[[Aspects of Love (novel)|Aspects of Love]]''\n*[[William Golding]] \u2013 ''[[The Inheritors (Golding novel)|The Inheritors]]''\n*[[Graham Greene]]\n**''[[The Quiet American]]''\n**''[[Loser Takes All]]''\n*[[Henri Ren\u00e9 Guieu]]\n**''L'Agonie du Verre''\n**''Commandos de l'Espace''\n**''Univers parall\u00e8les''\n*[[Robert A. Heinlein]] \u2013 ''[[Tunnel in the Sky]]''\n*[[Georgette Heyer]] \u2013 ''[[Bath Tangle]]''\n*[[Patricia Highsmith]] \u2013 ''[[The Talented Mr. Ripley]]''\n*[[Robert E. Howard]] and [[L. Sprague de Camp]] \u2013 ''[[Tales of Conan]]''\n*[[Aldous Huxley]] \u2013 ''[[The Genius and the Goddess]]''\n*[[Mac Hyman]] \u2013 ''[[No Time for Sergeants]]''\n*[[Roger Ikor]] \u2013 ''Les Eaux m\u00eal\u00e9es''\n*[[Dan Jacobson]] \u2013 ''The Trap''\n*[[Robin Jenkins]] \u2013 ''[[The Cone Gatherers]]''\n*[[Ruth Prawer Jhabvala]] \u2013 ''To Whom She Will''\n*[[MacKinlay Kantor]] \u2013 ''[[Andersonville (novel)|Andersonville]]''\n*[[Nikos Kazantzakis]] \u2013 ''[[The Last Temptation of Christ (novel)|The Last Temptation of Christ]]'' (''O Teleutaios Peirasmos'')\n*[[Ya\u015far Kemal]] \u2013 ''[[Memed, My Hawk]] (\u0130nce Memed)\n*[[Alexander Lernet-Holenia]] \u2013 ''[[Count Luna]]''\n*[[J\u00f3zef Mackiewicz]]\n**''Droga donik\u0105d'' (The Road to Nowhere)\n**''Karierowicz''\n*[[Alistair MacLean]] \u2013 ''[[HMS Ulysses (novel)|HMS Ulysses]]''\n*[[Norman Mailer]] \u2013 ''[[The Deer Park]]''\n*[[Gabriel Garc\u00eda M\u00e1rquez]]\n**''[[The Story of a Shipwrecked Sailor]] (Relato de un n\u00e1ufrago)''\n**''[[Leaf Storm]] (La Hojarasca)''\n*[[J. J. Marric]] \u2013 ''[[Gideon's Day]]''\n*[[Brian Moore (novelist)|Brian Moore]] \u2013 ''[[The Lonely Passion of Judith Hearne]]''\n*[[Vladimir Nabokov]] \u2013 ''[[Lolita]]''\n*[[Flannery O'Connor]] \u2013 ''[[A Good Man Is Hard